If I recommend it, it's because I've already tried it. Stay active and you will have concentration and a good memory. 🧠 
.
.

Exercise increases blood flow, which delivers more oxygen and nutrients to the brain, promoting the growth of new blood vessels and neurons. Additionally, it triggers the release of chemicals like neurotransmitters and hormones, such as endorphins and brain-derived neurotrophic factor (BDNF), which support cognitive health. This can lead to improved concentration and memory function over time.
.
.
Exercise stimulates the reward center of the brain, promoting a sense of pleasure and well-being. This surge in dopamine is linked to improved mood, motivation, and a positive outlook.
